The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 25 January is 182,535 (21,038.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 20 January, there were 8,773 new confirmed cases (1,011.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 13 January, there were 7,132 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 23% (1,641 extra cases).
